Due to a widespread iatrogenic contamination in the 1960’s, Egypt currently has the highest hepatitis C prevalence worldwide, with up to 30% seropositivity in individuals over 50. It is thought that hospitals play a major part in sustaining the current epidemic dynamics. Indeed, hospitalized patients undergo a high number of invasive procedures during which they are at-risk of acquiring HCV, all the more so that compliance with infection control recommendations is not perfect. the prevalence is particularly high among patients admitted to hospitals, due to their age and medical history. Moreover,